event: content_block_stop
data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"## Multi-Agent Security Incident Response — Platform Discovery Report\n\nAll discovery probes completed. Here is the complete inventory of templates, frameworks, tools, and MCP servers available for building the system.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Orchestration Frameworks\n\n| Framework | Status | Endpoint | Suitability |\n|-----------|:------:|----------|-------------|\n| **LangGraph** | ✅ Healthy | `openagentic-langgraph:3100` | **Primary choice** — StateGraph with conditional routing, human-in-the-loop, iterative loops |\n| **CrewAI** | ✅ Healthy | `openagentic-crewai:3200` | **Good alternative** — role-based multi-agent with built-in delegation |\n| **Flowise** | ❌ Unhealthy | `openagentic-api:8000/api/flowise-workspace` | Unavailable — skip for this build |\n\n> **Recommendation:** Use **LangGraph** (the platform default) for the incident response system. Its `StateGraph` model maps directly to incident lifecycle states (triage → investigate → remediate → resolve) with conditional edges and interrupt gates.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Agent Templates\n\nFour pre-built templates exist. The **AIOps** template is the closest starting point.\n\n| Template | ID | Roles | Built-in Tools | Fit |\n|----------|----|-------|----------------|:---:|\n| **AIOps Agent** | `aiops` | monitor, investigator, responder | `prometheus_query`, `k8s_get_pods`, `k8s_get_logs`, `k8s_describe`, `k8s_scale`, `k8s_restart` | ✅ High |\n| **Research Agent** | `research` | researcher, analyzer | `web_search`, `web_fetch` | ⚠️ Partial — useful for CVE/threat intel lookup |\n| **Code Assistant** | `code_assistant` | analyst, generator, reviewer | `openagentic_read_file`, `openagentic_write_file`, `openagentic_search`, `openagentic_execute` | ⚠️ Partial — useful for config analysis |\n| **Data Pipeline** | `data_pipeline` | extractor, transformer, loader | `web_fetch`, `openagentic_execute` | ❌ Low |\n\n---\n\n## 3. MCP Tool Inventory\n\n### 3a. Available MCP Servers (8 total)\n\n| MCP Server | Domain | Key Tools |\n|------------|--------|-----------|\n| **oap-azure-mcp** | Azure ARM/Graph | `azure_arm_execute`, `azure_graph_execute`, `azure_keyvault_secret`, `azure_cost_query` |\n| **oap-aws-mcp** | AWS Cloud | `call_aws`, `aws_list_ec2`, `aws_list_s3`, `aws_cost_summary` |\n| **oap-web-mcp** | Web/OSINT | `web_search`, `web_fetch`, `web_news_search` |\n| **oap-flowise-mcp** | Workflow Mgmt | `flowise_create_agentflow`, `flowise_execute_chatflow` |\n| **oap-diagram-mcp** | Visualization | `create_diagram` |\n| **oap-admin-mcp** | Platform Admin | `system_health`, `user_list`, `audit_logs` |\n| **oap-memory-mcp** | State/Memory | `memory_store`, `memory_recall`, `memory_search` |\n| **oap-knowledge-mcp** | Tool Docs | `suggest_tools_for_task`, `get_tool_examples` |\n\n### 3b. Tools by Category (Relevant to Incident Response)\n\n| Category | Tools | IR Role |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| **Monitoring** | `prometheus_query`, `prometheus_alerts` | Alert ingestion, metric correlation |\n| **Kubernetes** | `k8s_get_pods`, `k8s_get_logs`, `k8s_describe`, `k8s_scale`, `k8s_restart` | Investigation, remediation |\n| **Log Search** | `loki_search_errors` (via admin MCP) | Forensic log correlation |\n| **Incident Mgmt** | `incident_create`, `incident_update_status`, `incident_escalate`, `incident_resolve` (via admin MCP) | Full incident lifecycle |\n| **Cloud (Azure)** | `azure_arm_execute`, `azure_keyvault_secret` | Cloud resource investigation, secret rotation |\n| **Cloud (AWS)** | `call_aws`, `aws_list_ec2` | AWS resource investigation |\n| **Web/OSINT** | `web_search`, `web_fetch` | CVE lookup, threat intelligence |\n| **Memory** | `memory_store`, `memory_recall` | Cross-agent state persistence |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Proposed Agent Architecture\n\nBased on the discovery and our previous design session, here is the mapping of available resources to the three-agent architecture:\n\n```diagram\n{\n  \"type\": \"flowchart\",\n  \"title\": \"Security Incident Response — Multi-Agent Architecture\",\n  \"layout\": \"vertical\",\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\"id\": \"alerts\", \"label\": \"Prometheus\\nAlertmanager\", \"shape\": \"parallelogram\", \"color\": \"warning\"},\n    {\"id\": \"triage\", \"label\": \"TriageAgent\\n(First Responder)\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"primary\"},\n    {\"id\": \"forensics\", \"label\": \"ForensicsAgent\\n(Deep Investigator)\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"info\"},\n    {\"id\": \"gate\", \"label\": \"Human Gate\\n(P1 Only)\", \"shape\": \"diamond\", \"color\": \"warning\"},\n    {\"id\": \"remediation\", \"label\": \"RemediationAgent\\n(Executor)\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"success\"},\n    {\"id\": \"resolved\", \"label\": \"Incident\\nResolved\", \"shape\": \"circle\", \"color\": \"success\"},\n    {\"id\": \"escalate\", \"label\": \"Escalate to\\nHuman\", \"shape\": \"circle\", \"color\": \"error\"}\n  ],\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\"source\": \"alerts\", \"target\": \"triage\", \"label\": \"Webhook / Poll\"},\n    {\"source\": \"triage\", \"target\": \"forensics\", \"label\": \"Incident Created\"},\n    {\"source\": \"forensics\", \"target\": \"gate\", \"label\": \"Investigation Complete\"},\n    {\"source\": \"gate\", \"target\": \"remediation\", \"label\": \"P2-P4: Auto\", \"style\": \"solid\"},\n    {\"source\": \"gate\", \"target\": \"escalate\", \"label\": \"P1: Human Approval\", \"style\": \"dashed\"},\n    {\"source\": \"remediation\", \"target\": \"resolved\", \"label\": \"Success\"},\n    {\"source\": \"remediation\", \"target\": \"escalate\", \"label\": \"Failed\", \"style\": \"dashed\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Agent ↔ Tool Assignment\n\n| Agent | Template Base | Assigned Tools | Framework |\n|-------|--------------|----------------|-----------|\n| **TriageAgent** | `aiops` (monitor role) | `prometheus_alerts`, `loki_search_errors`, `incident_list`, `incident_create` | LangGraph `StateGraph` |\n| **ForensicsAgent** | `aiops` (investigator role) + `research` | `loki_search_errors`, `k8s_get_pods`, `k8s_get_logs`, `k8s_describe`, `web_search`, `incident_update_status` | LangGraph `StateGraph` |\n| **RemediationAgent** | `aiops` (responder role) | `k8s_restart`, `k8s_scale`, `k8s_cluster_health`, `incident_link_runbook`, `incident_resolve`, `incident_escalate` | LangGraph `StateGraph` + human interrupt |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Key Findings & Constraints\n\n| Finding | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---------|--------|------------|\n| **Flowise is unhealthy** | Cannot use visual flow builder | Use LangGraph code-based deployment |\n| **No dedicated SIEM MCP** | No native SIEM/SOAR integration | Combine `prometheus_alerts` + `loki_search_errors` + `web_search` as composite detection layer |\n| **AIOps template is closest** | 80% tool overlap with IR needs | Extend with `incident_*` and `web_search` tools |\n| **8 MCP servers available** | Rich tool ecosystem | 6 of 8 MCPs are directly relevant to IR |\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n\nReady to proceed to design and code generation. Options:\n\n1. **`design_custom_agent`** — Generate a full agent spec from natural language for each of the three agents\n2. **`create_agent_from_template`** — Start from the `aiops` template and extend with additional tools\n3. **`generate_agent_code`** — Produce deployable LangGraph Python code from a spec\n4. **`deploy_agent`** — Deploy to the live LangGraph service\n\nWant me to proceed with designing the three-agent system and generating the LangGraph code?"}

